Big thanks to Decibelles for giving me the go-ahead to delete and repost.

This article's title, , is lifted from Fredy Perlman's The Continuing Appeal of Nationalism, which is a fantastic piece all-around.

For me, this is about a particular kind of social isolation that leaves its practitioners, myself included, particularly vulnerable  and since this is the sort of paranoia that affects me personally, I figured it would translate well into a spooky scary SCP. Normies can take that or leave it, as far as I'm concerned, but I do want to make it clear where this article coming from.








